{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":627,"text":"So, we used to solve big problems."},{"time":5263,"text":"On July 21st, 1969,"},{"time":8783,"text":"Buzz Aldrin climbed out of Apollo 11's lunar module"},{"time":12370,"text":"and descended onto the Sea of Tranquility."},{"time":15927,"text":"Armstrong and Aldrin were alone,"},{"time":18657,"text":"but their presence on the moon's gray surface"},{"time":20943,"text":"was the culmination of a convulsive, collective effort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26074,"text":"The Apollo program was the greatest"},{"time":28118,"text":"peacetime mobilization"},{"time":29855,"text":"in the history of the United States."},{"time":31793,"text":"To get to the moon, NASA spent"},{"time":33289,"text":"around 180 billion dollars in today's money,"},{"time":37028,"text":"or four percent of the federal budget."},{"time":39564,"text":"Apollo employed around 400,000 people"},{"time":42868,"text":"and demanded the collaboration of 20,000"},{"time":45706,"text":"companies, universities and government agencies."},{"time":49402,"text":"People died, including the crew of Apollo 1."},{"time":53346,"text":"But before the Apollo program ended,"},{"time":56947,"text":"24 men flew to the moon."},{"time":59176,"text":"Twelve walked on its surface, of whom Aldrin,"},{"time":62250,"text":"following the death of Armstrong last year,"},{"time":64603,"text":"is now the most senior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66689,"text":"So why did they go?"},{"time":68674,"text":"They didn't bring much back:"},{"time":70591,"text":"841 pounds of old rocks,"},{"time":73250,"text":"and something all 24 later emphasized --"},{"time":77705,"text":"a new sense of the smallness"},{"time":80567,"text":"and the fragility of our common home."},{"time":83510,"text":"Why did they go? The cynical answer is they went"},{"time":86590,"text":"because President Kennedy wanted to show"},{"time":88566,"text":"the Soviets that his nation had the better rockets."},{"time":92673,"text":"But Kennedy's own words at Rice University in 1962"},{"time":97145,"text":"provide a better clue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99043,"text":"(Video) John F. Kennedy: But why, some say, the moon?"},{"time":101566,"text":"Why choose this as our goal?"},{"time":104510,"text":"And they may well ask,"},{"time":106433,"text":"why climb the highest mountain?"},{"time":109012,"text":"Why, 35 years ago, fly the Atlantic?"},{"time":113028,"text":"Why does Rice play Texas?"},{"time":115212,"text":"We choose to go to the moon."},{"time":117823,"text":"We choose to go to the moon."},{"time":120400,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":125670,"text":"We choose to go to the moon in this decade,"},{"time":128584,"text":"and do the other things,"},{"time":130231,"text":"not because they are easy, but because they are hard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134560,"text":"Jason Pontin: To contemporaries,"},{"time":136730,"text":"Apollo wasn't only a victory of West over East"},{"time":139983,"text":"in the Cold War."},{"time":141198,"text":"At the time, the strongest emotion"},{"time":143203,"text":"was of wonder"},{"time":144928,"text":"at the transcendent powers of technology."},{"time":148527,"text":"They went because it was a big thing to do."},{"time":153946,"text":"Landing on the moon occurred in the context"},{"time":156466,"text":"of a long series of technological triumphs."},{"time":159631,"text":"The first half of the 20th century produced"},{"time":162144,"text":"the assembly line and the airplane,"},{"time":164280,"text":"penicillin and a vaccine for tuberculosis."},{"time":167554,"text":"In the middle years of the century,"},{"time":168856,"text":"polio was eradicated and smallpox eliminated."},{"time":172548,"text":"Technology itself seemed to possess"},{"time":174545,"text":"what Alvin Toffler in 1970"},{"time":177129,"text":"called \"accelerative thrust.\""},{"time":179963,"text":"For most of human history,"},{"time":181807,"text":"we could go no faster than a horse"},{"time":184095,"text":"or a boat with a sail,"},{"time":186196,"text":"but in 1969, the crew of Apollo 10"},{"time":188597,"text":"flew at 25,000 miles an hour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192480,"text":"Since 1970, no human beings"},{"time":195380,"text":"have been back to the moon."},{"time":197262,"text":"No one has traveled faster than the crew"},{"time":199481,"text":"of Apollo 10,"},{"time":201087,"text":"and blithe optimism about technology's powers"},{"time":204859,"text":"has evaporated"},{"time":206761,"text":"as big problems we had imagined technology would solve,"},{"time":210332,"text":"such as going to Mars,"},{"time":212635,"text":"creating clean energy, curing cancer,"},{"time":215966,"text":"or feeding the world have come to seem"},{"time":218775,"text":"intractably hard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221464,"text":"I remember watching the liftoff of Apollo 17."},{"time":225173,"text":"I was five years old,"},{"time":227222,"text":"and my mother told me not to stare"},{"time":229590,"text":"at the fiery exhaust of a Saturn V rocket."},{"time":232725,"text":"I vaguely knew this was to be the last"},{"time":235166,"text":"of the moon missions,"},{"time":236704,"text":"but I was absolutely certain there would be"},{"time":240470,"text":"Mars colonies in my lifetime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243780,"text":"So \"Something happened"},{"time":246343,"text":"to our capacity to solve big problems with technology\""},{"time":250526,"text":"has become a commonplace."},{"time":252918,"text":"You hear it all the time."},{"time":254308,"text":"We've heard it over the last two days here at TED."},{"time":257720,"text":"It feels as if technologists have diverted us"},{"time":261688,"text":"and enriched themselves with trivial toys,"},{"time":264373,"text":"with things like iPhones and apps and social media,"},{"time":267878,"text":"or algorithms that speed automated trading."},{"time":271497,"text":"There's nothing wrong with most of these things."},{"time":273891,"text":"They've expanded and enriched our lives."},{"time":276972,"text":"But they don't solve humanity's big problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281673,"text":"What happened?"},{"time":282886,"text":"So there is a parochial explanation in Silicon Valley,"},{"time":287800,"text":"which admits that it has been funding less ambitious companies"},{"time":291245,"text":"than it did in the years when it financed"},{"time":293547,"text":"Intel, Microsoft, Apple and Genentech."},{"time":296705,"text":"Silicon Valley says the markets are to blame,"},{"time":299265,"text":"in particular the incentives that venture capitalists"},{"time":302182,"text":"offer to entrepreneurs."},{"time":303762,"text":"Silicon Valley says that venture investing"},{"time":305878,"text":"shifted away from funding transformational ideas"},{"time":309741,"text":"and towards funding incremental problems"},{"time":312680,"text":"or even fake problems."},{"time":314728,"text":"But I don't think that explanation is good enough."},{"time":317479,"text":"It mostly explains what's wrong with Silicon Valley."},{"time":321363,"text":"Even when venture capitalists were at their most"},{"time":324013,"text":"risk-happy, they preferred small investments,"},{"time":326852,"text":"tiny investments that offered an exit within 10 years."},{"time":330716,"text":"V.C.s have always struggled"},{"time":333035,"text":"to invest profitably in technologies such as energy"},{"time":336110,"text":"whose capital requirements are huge"},{"time":338304,"text":"and whose development is long and lengthy,"},{"time":341012,"text":"and V.C.s have never, never funded the development"},{"time":344169,"text":"of technologies meant to solve big problems"},{"time":347167,"text":"that possess no immediate commercial value."},{"time":349861,"text":"No, the reasons we can't solve big problems"},{"time":352073,"text":"are more complicated and more profound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356155,"text":"Sometimes we choose not to solve big problems."},{"time":359142,"text":"We could go to Mars if we want."},{"time":361560,"text":"NASA even has the outline of a plan."},{"time":364427,"text":"But going to Mars would follow a political decision"},{"time":367916,"text":"with popular appeal, and that will never happen."},{"time":371270,"text":"We won't go to Mars, because everyone thinks"},{"time":374012,"text":"there are more important things"},{"time":375961,"text":"to do here on Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378248,"text":"Sometimes, we can't solve big problems"},{"time":381292,"text":"because our political systems fail."},{"time":383796,"text":"Today, less than two percent"},{"time":385894,"text":"of the world's energy consumption"},{"time":387581,"text":"derives from advanced, renewable sources"},{"time":389747,"text":"such as solar, wind and biofuels,"},{"time":392625,"text":"less than two percent,"},{"time":394207,"text":"and the reason is purely economic."},{"time":396311,"text":"Coal and natural gas are cheaper"},{"time":398504,"text":"than solar and wind,"},{"time":400249,"text":"and petroleum is cheaper than biofuels."},{"time":402768,"text":"We want alternative energy sources"},{"time":405449,"text":"that can compete on price. None exist."},{"time":408450,"text":"Now, technologists, business leaders"},{"time":411155,"text":"and economists all basically agree"},{"time":413651,"text":"on what national policies and international treaties"},{"time":417152,"text":"would spur the development of alternative energy:"},{"time":420436,"text":"mostly, a significant increase in energy"},{"time":423151,"text":"research and development,"},{"time":424568,"text":"and some kind of price on carbon."},{"time":427363,"text":"But there's no hope in the present political climate"},{"time":430567,"text":"that we will see U.S. energy policy"},{"time":432960,"text":"or international treaties that reflect that consensus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437727,"text":"Sometimes, big problems that had seemed technological"},{"time":442211,"text":"turn out not to be so."},{"time":444110,"text":"Famines were long understood to be caused"},{"time":447328,"text":"by failures in food supply."},{"time":449736,"text":"But 30 years of research have taught us"},{"time":451991,"text":"that famines are political crises"},{"time":454659,"text":"that catastrophically affect food distribution."},{"time":458173,"text":"Technology can improve things like crop yields"},{"time":461136,"text":"or systems for storing and transporting food,"},{"time":465379,"text":"but there will be famines so long as there are bad governments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470624,"text":"Finally, big problems sometimes elude solution"},{"time":474139,"text":"because we don't really understand the problem."},{"time":477605,"text":"President Nixon declared war on cancer in 1971,"},{"time":482549,"text":"but we soon discovered"},{"time":483962,"text":"there are many kinds of cancer,"},{"time":486495,"text":"most of them fiendishly resistant to therapy,"},{"time":490061,"text":"and it is only in the last 10 years"},{"time":492271,"text":"that effective, viable therapies"},{"time":494818,"text":"have come to seem real."},{"time":496875,"text":"Hard problems are hard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499925,"text":"It's not true that we can't solve big problems through technology."},{"time":504407,"text":"We can, we must, but these four elements"},{"time":508123,"text":"must all be present:"},{"time":509878,"text":"Political leaders and the public"},{"time":511822,"text":"must care to solve a problem;"},{"time":513564,"text":"institutions must support its solution;"},{"time":516735,"text":"It must really be a technological problem;"},{"time":519810,"text":"and we must understand it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523661,"text":"The Apollo mission,"},{"time":525108,"text":"which has become a kind of metaphor"},{"time":527845,"text":"for technology's capacity to solve big problems,"},{"time":531029,"text":"met these criteria."},{"time":533240,"text":"But it is an irreproducible model for the future."},{"time":536667,"text":"It is not 1961."},{"time":538491,"text":"There is no galvanizing contest like the Cold War,"},{"time":542582,"text":"no politician like John Kennedy"},{"time":544941,"text":"who can heroize the difficult and the dangerous,"},{"time":548132,"text":"and no popular science fictional mythology"},{"time":551477,"text":"such as exploring the solar system."},{"time":554583,"text":"Most of all, going to the moon"},{"time":556985,"text":"turned out to be easy."},{"time":558847,"text":"It was just three days away."},{"time":560895,"text":"And arguably it wasn't even solving"},{"time":563780,"text":"much of a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566384,"text":"We are left alone with our day,"},{"time":570464,"text":"and the solutions of the future will be harder won."},{"time":575941,"text":"God knows, we don't lack for the challenges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578726,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579880,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}